BIG CONVOY nodded, &quot;But don&#39;t let over confidence get the better of
you. Just because you can fly doen&#39;t mean you can&#39;t be brought down.&quot;

Hefting his weapon CONVOY motioned for BREAK and MACK KICK to follow
him as he followed TUSCON. &quot;Single file now and by the numbers, we
don&#39;t have a second time for this one.&quot;

The others nodded as they fell in step and began to move.

The ground for TUSCON quickly sloped down as once again he made his
way. As it was once before all communication systems were down and
even IFF sensors were muffled as parts of them required a low level
form of radio transmission, if only passive a one. There was no way to
transmit data on radio wave.

As he moved the cave was lit by glowing phosphorescent rocks of some
sort sitting in the roof of the cave, their lights creating an odd
scintillating color as they bounced off some of the more reflective
surfaces of other stones.

Ahead of him the cave tunnel he was in continued to drop and oddly
enough his sensor range was actually getting smaller and shorter as he
moved. His senses worked just fine, but radar and sonar were getting
shorter and shorter pings as if something was interfering.

However he was beginning to pick up a low level hum.

